This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it deals with automatic identification and expansion of ambiguous abbreviations in biomedical natural language processing applications. The use of BioELMo and bidirectional LSTMs also suggests that this paper may fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
